  <description type="morphology">Stem and branch leaves lanceolate, ovate-lanceolate, broadly ovate-lanceolate, oval, or deltoid, 1–3 × 0.5–1.2 mm; costa single, weak, 1/4–3/4 leaf length, or double, short; laminal cells fusiform to linear, 4–8:1; medial cells 25–80 × 5–11 µm. Sexual condition autoicous, often gonioautoicous. Seta 0.4–3.9 mm. Capsule immersed to exserted, 1–2.3 × 0.4–1 mm; operculum 0.5–1.1 × 0.3–0.6 mm; exostome teeth smooth, minutely papillose, or occasionally granulose. Spores 18–30 µm.</description>
